Process called "calculate_total_tests" that takes isolation_results as IsolationTestResults, security_results as SecurityTestResults, resource_results as ResourceTestResults, policy_results as PolicyTestResults, audit_results as AuditTestResults, performance_results as PerformanceTestResults, edge_case_results as EdgeCaseTestResults, integration_results as IntegrationTestResults, security_scan_results as SecurityScanResults returns Integer:
    Let total be 0
    
    Note: Count isolation tests
    Let total be total + 8  Note: filesystem, network, process, memory, syscall, inter-plugin, host protection, escape prevention
    
    Note: Count security tests  
    Let total be total + 8  Note: policy enforcement, privilege escalation, unauthorized access, malicious code, input validation, output sanitization, crypto, secure comm
    
    Note: Count resource tests
    Let total be total + 8  Note: memory, cpu, disk, network, file handles, threads, timeout, cleanup
    
    Note: Count policy tests
    Let total be total + 8  Note: creation, validation, enforcement, inheritance, conflicts, updates, compliance, violations
    
    Note: Count audit tests
    Let total be total + 8  Note: event logging, activity tracking, violation reporting, compliance monitoring, forensic analysis, audit integrity, real-time alerts, data retention
    
    Note: Count performance tests
    Let total be total + 8  Note: sandbox creation, policy evaluation, resource monitoring, audit logging, isolation overhead, cleanup, concurrent sandbox, memory efficiency
    
    Note: Count edge case tests
    Let total be total + 8  Note: malformed plugins, resource exhaustion, sandbox corruption, policy edge cases, concurrent violations, system limits, nested scenarios, emergency shutdown
    
    Note: Count integration tests
    Let total be total + 8  Note: API integration, management integration, loading integration, discovery integration, architecture integration, e2e security, multi-plugin, production readiness
    
    Note: Count security scan tests
    Let total be total + 8  Note: vulnerability scan, penetration tests, compliance check, threat model, attack vectors, defense mechanisms, baseline validation, incident response
    
    Return total

Process called "extract_critical_failures" that takes isolation_results as IsolationTestResults, security_results as SecurityTestResults, resource_results as ResourceTestResults, policy_results as PolicyTestResults, audit_results as AuditTestResults, performance_results as PerformanceTestResults, edge_case_results as EdgeCaseTestResults, integration_results as IntegrationTestResults, security_scan_results as SecurityScanResults returns List[String]:
    Let critical_failures be list containing
    
    Note: Check for critical security failures
    If security_results.policy_enforcement.passed is false:
        Add "CRITICAL: Security policy enforcement failed" to critical_failures
    
    If security_results.privilege_escalation_prevention.passed is false:
        Add "CRITICAL: Privilege escalation prevention failed" to critical_failures
    
    If isolation_results.sandbox_escape_prevention.passed is false:
        Add "CRITICAL: Sandbox escape prevention failed" to critical_failures
    
    If security_scan_results.vulnerability_scan.passed is false:
        Add "CRITICAL: Vulnerability scan detected critical issues" to critical_failures
    
    Note: Check for critical resource failures
    If resource_results.memory_limits.passed is false:
        Add "CRITICAL: Memory limit enforcement failed" to critical_failures
    
    Note: Check for critical audit failures
    If audit_results.audit_trail_integrity.passed is false:
        Add "CRITICAL: Audit trail integrity compromised" to critical_failures
    
    Return critical_failures

Note: Main entry point for sandboxing tests
Process called "main":
    Let test_report be run_sandboxing_tests
    
    Note: Display comprehensive test results
    Display "=== Runa Advanced Plugins Sandboxing Test Report ==="
    Display format("Test execution completed at: {}", test_report.timestamp)
    Display format("Total tests run: {}", test_report.total_tests_run)
    Display format("Tests passed: {}", test_report.tests_passed)
    Display format("Tests failed: {}", test_report.tests_failed)
    Display format("Test duration: {} ms", test_report.test_duration_ms)
    
    Note: Display critical failures if any
    If test_report.critical_failures.length > 0:
        Display "=== CRITICAL FAILURES ==="
        For Each failure in test_report.critical_failures:
            Display format("❌ {}", failure)
    
    Note: Display security violations if any
    If test_report.security_violations.length > 0:
        Display "=== SECURITY VIOLATIONS ==="
        For Each violation in test_report.security_violations:
            Display format("🚨 {}", violation)
    
    Note: Display performance warnings if any
    If test_report.performance_warnings.length > 0:
        Display "=== PERFORMANCE WARNINGS ==="
        For Each warning in test_report.performance_warnings:
            Display format("⚠️ {}", warning)
    
    Note: Display overall status
    If test_report.tests_failed is 0 and test_report.critical_failures.length is 0:
        Display "✅ All sandboxing tests passed - System ready for production"
    Else:
        Display "❌ Some tests failed - Review failures before production deployment"
    
    Display "=== End of Sandboxing Test Report ==="